{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a60fa558-190d-4b2b-9174-cdec0cd316bf","content":"Yes, you **will** hit compatibility issues. MSTest v3 dropped support for some of your target frameworks:\n\n- **`net5.0`** — .NET 5 is not supported by MSTest v3. You'll need to upgrade to **`net6.0`** or later.\n- **`net462`** — .NET Framework versions older than 4.6.2 are dropped, but 4.6.2 itself is still supported, so this one is fine.\n- **`netcoreapp3.1`** — .NET Core 3.1 is not supported by MSTest v3. You'll need to upgrade to **`net6.0`** or later.\n\n**Summary of required changes:**\n| Target | Status | Action |\n|---|---|---|\n| `net5.0` | ❌ Dropped | Replace with `net6.0`+ |\n| `netcoreapp3.1` | ❌ Dropped | Replace with `net6.0`+ |\n| `net462` | ✅ Supported | No change needed |\n\nWould you like me to proceed with the migration? I can update the target frameworks and upgrade the MSTest packages to v3.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"0f76ed75-5288-4d8f-b11d-fc82fdd35dc6","outputTokens":281,"requestId":"042F:22EFE:5FCBA3:709862:69E83213"},"id":"f93a27f9-124b-4e09-a5b5-42d0c530024e","timestamp":"2026-04-22T02:27:39.032Z","parentId":"2f5893ae-ed09-4fff-96e9-ee6a910b5180"}
